  "text": "Sclerosing stromal tumors are rare sex chord stromal tumors. They constitute less than 5 percent of sex chord stromal tumors (2) . It was first reported in 1973 by Chalvardjian and Scully [CITATION_1] . Later Peng et al. reported 114 cases until 2003 [CITATION_2] . SSTs usually present in the second and third decade in contrast to other stromal tumors which are most common in the fifth and sixth decade [CITATION_3] 8) . The mean age of SSTs at diagnosis is 28 (2) .",
